1
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,479
Deputy Captain Inoue Kamakura

2
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:40,320
fought bravely

3
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:47,000
died in battle.

4
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,210
Alright, I understand.

5
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:53,640
Through countless lives in the three realms,

6
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:04,960
Year after year passes without a breeze.

7
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:21,800
By the Bridge of Helplessness, watching the cycle of rebirth,

8
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:34,720
Guiding souls and listening to ghostly voices.

9
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,680
Retribution.

10
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,720
Old man,

11
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,880
I'm sending you back today.

12
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,720
Inoue Mansion.

13
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,000
Mr. Inoue Akira.

14
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,480
Yesterday, in an enemy

15
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,720
attack on the Sixth Air Base,

16
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,400
Deputy Commander Inoue Kamakura

17
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,320
fought bravely

18
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,560
and died heroically.

19
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,450
Cherry blossom season is coming soon.

20
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:27,160
I've had them learn this dance especially.

21
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,800
Please watch, General.

22
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,200
It's like being back home

23
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,930
during cherry blossom season.

24
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:41,480
How thoughtful of you, Inoue.

25
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,800
Thank you for your hard work.

26
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:47,159
Have another drink.

27
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,840
Master.

28
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,720
Impossible.

29
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,240
I am too old now.

30
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:05,580
I can't kill my enemies with my own hands.

31
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:09,410
I've missed the chance to avenge all of you brothers,

32
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:12,040
and over ten thousand deceased villagers

33
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,960
from Sanzao Island.

34
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,620
I've lost the perfect opportunity for revenge.

35
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:21,280
I have failed my ancestors

36
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:25,080
and the spirits of all my brothers.

37
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:32,720
I am so useless!

38
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,760
Master.

39
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:45,840
Master.

40
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,760
Sir,

41
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:52,490
there are some merchants from Sanzao Island requesting to see you.

42
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,960
Bring them in.

43
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,600
We need to

44
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:13,120
get an explanation from Master Geng about this matter.

45
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,120
Let's verify it.

46
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,320
Master Geng.

47
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:17,920
We've heard that

48
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,720
someone in Macao has spread news

49
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,800
that the Japanese troops on Sanzao Island

50
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,040
will lift the maritime ban in a couple of days

51
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,120
and allow islanders to go fishing at sea.

52
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,400
Is this true?

53
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,480
That can't be right.

54
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:37,600
Since these Japanese devils occupied the island,

55
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,840
they've banned maritime activities

56
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,440
for more than four years now.

57
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:42,480
Where did you

58
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,809
hear this information?

59
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,320
Master Geng,

60
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,080
it was overheard by someone

61
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,160
who works at the Japanese consulate.

62
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,290
This information should be reliable.

63
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,480
Let me think

64
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,240
about this matter a bit more.

65
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,160
Once I figure it out,

66
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,120
I'll let you all know.

67
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,410
I'll send someone to gather information.

68
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,960
I'll notify everyone when I have news.

69
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,640
At that time,

70
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:14,200
we'll discuss it thoroughly.

71
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:14,920
Alright, Mr. Ye,

72
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:15,880
we'll take our leave now.

73
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,760
Goodbye.

74
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,090
Lao Yi, see them out.

75
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:00,400
Lao Yi.

76
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,360
Arrange for someone to find out

77
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,320
if Director Shen from the National Government

78
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,520
has returned yet.

79
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,320
I have important matters

80
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,450
to discuss with him.

81
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,160
Make way.

82
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:28,920
Excuse me.

83
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:29,840
Let me through.

84
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,160
Step aside.

85
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:34,600
Director.

86
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:00,760
Director

87
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,120
please take a break.

88
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,560
Zheng,

89
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,800
what's been happening

90
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,280
with you guys these days?

91
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:08,600
Our

92
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,080
informant in the Portuguese police reported that

93
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:12,640
something happened today.

94
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:16,080
A special police squad leader from

95
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,040
the Sanzao Island Sixth Air Base

96
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,760
came to Macau with his men.

97
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,960
The Ba Qu guys wanted revenge

98
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,240
and sent people to kill them.

99
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:25,720
A gunfight broke out

100
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,800
and several people were injured.

101
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,000
What happened then?

102
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:29,720
Well,

103
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,560
the action team from Macau Rong Agency

104
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,480
rescued them.

105
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,090
The assassination failed.

106
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,640
How did the Rong Agency people

107
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,370
know about the assassination?

108
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:39,480
The information must have leaked.

109
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,280
The Ba Qu guys from Anlan Hall

110
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:44,220
aren't very careful with their operations.

111
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,610
Make arrangements.

112
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:47,120
I'll go to Anlan Hall.

113
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:48,520
Now?

114
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,640
Right now.

115
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,480
Let's do this.

116
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,840
Quickly contact our people on the island first

117
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,400
and clarify the situation.

118
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,410
What's the story with the Japanese

119
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:26,160
lifting the maritime ban?

120
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,000
Who exactly is allowed to go to sea

121
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,880
and when are they permitted to do so?

122
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:31,760
After going out to sea,

123
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:34,040
are there any gunboats monitoring the island?

124
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,480
Go find out about these things.

125
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,040
Yes,

126
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,560
I'll take care of it right away.

127
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,920
I'm thinking

128
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:42,080
if this is true,

129
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,240
perhaps we can make good use of it.

130
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:50,250
Once we figure everything out,

131
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,600
we might be able to get

132
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,600
my brother's family off the island.

133
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,720
Sir,

134
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:02,280
what if it's a trap?

135
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:04,000
Well,

136
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,640
I also have a bad feeling

137
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,920
that something might be wrong with this.

138
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:12,960
Indeed,

139
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:14,720
when have the Japanese on the island

140
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:17,160
ever shown such kindness?

141
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,640
They've actually lifted the sea ban

142
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,760
and allowed villagers to go fishing.

143
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,240
This is just too strange.

144
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,060
First, contact the people on the island.

145
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,640
Keep it quiet.

146
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:36,600
Mr. Ye.

147
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:39,080
Director Shen from the National Government has arrived.

148
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:39,960
Mr. Ye.

149
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:40,840
Hello.

150
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,080
Director Shen.

151
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,280
I was just about to send someone for you.

152
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,000
What brings you here in such a hurry?

153
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,800
Is it urgent?

154
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:45,760
What a coincidence.

155
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,760
I just returned to Macau from out of town.

156
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,360
I heard that the Sanzao Island's

157
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,200
special police captain has arrived in Macau.

158
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,000
Is that right?

159
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,860
We've brought our men right away.

160
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:56,080
News travels fast.

161
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:57,600
Don't mind.

162
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:00,640
Our Military Intelligence has some informants

163
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,570
in the Portuguese police in Macau.

164
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,320
Director Shen.

165
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,040
You're one step too late.

166
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:13,080
That Japanese special police captain

167
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,320
got away from us.

168
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,840
What a shame.

169
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:41,720
Mr. Ye.

170
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,960
I understand.

171
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,360
I have something to say

172
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,720
that you might not like.

173
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:48,840
I'm a straightforward man.

174
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,200
Please speak freely.

175
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:52,160
Your operation failed

176
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:54,400
because there must be

177
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,780
a Japanese spy among your District 8 men.

178
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:00,200
Impossible.

179
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:02,880
Among my District 8 men,

180
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:05,140
there are no such cowards as you suggest.

181
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:06,640
Macau today

182
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:08,920
is like Shanghai's isolated island in the past,

183
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:12,120
where spies from all over the world operate.

184
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:14,600
They

185
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,800
gather military intelligence on each other,

186
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,360
exchange benefits,

187
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:21,200
and raise war funds.

188
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,520
Of course.

189
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,540
There are usually situations like this.

190
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,240
Our people

191
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,280
might be bought with large sums of money

192
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,720
to work for them.

193
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:33,520
Similarly,

194
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,640
their people

195
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,400
can also be bought by us

196
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,800
to work for us.

197
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:39,840
We've dealt with

198
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:42,100
situations like this many times before.

199
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:44,200
So I'm certain

200
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,560
that your operation's failure

201
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:48,760
must be due to an inside problem.

202
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,480
How can you be so sure?

203
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,280
Mr. Ye,

204
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,600
if necessary,

205
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,930
our Military Statistics Bureau can help.

206
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:01,640
Impossible.

207
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,960
You're overthinking this.

208
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,200
Perhaps I am overthinking it.

209
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:12,280
Come in.

210
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,340
Please have a seat.

211
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,760
Director Shen, you're well-informed.

212
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,960
I need to ask you something.

213
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,200
There's a rumor

214
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,640
going around outside.

215
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,240
Sanzao Island

216
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,840
will soon lift its maritime ban.

217
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:33,480
They're planning to allow

218
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,940
the island's fishermen to go fishing at sea.

219
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:38,160
Do you think this is reliable?

220
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,480
I'm sorry,

221
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:42,940
but what does lifting the maritime ban mean?

222
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,360
Since February of 1938,

223
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:48,640
after the Japanese occupied Sanzao Island,

224
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:51,000
they established naval and air force bases there

225
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,360
and have forbidden fishermen from going to sea,

226
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:55,040
for four or five years now.

227
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:56,920
Outsiders can't get in,

228
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,570
and insiders can't get out.

229
00:16:58,640 --> 00:17:00,760
Now this news suddenly comes out.

230
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:03,760
I'm also very surprised.

231
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,359
Interesting.

232
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:08,280
Four or five years.

233
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:10,560
This is indeed suspicious.

234
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,650
We should definitely look into it.

235
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,480
Do you have any thoughts?

236
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:20,599
Some gentry from Sanzao Island

237
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:23,040
who fled to Macau have approached me.

238
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:26,200
They want to use this opportunity

239
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:27,839
to rescue

240
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:30,160
their families from the island.

241
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,760
But I think,

242
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,600
if this is true,

243
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:37,120
perhaps I could also

244
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,520
bring my brother's family

245
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:40,800
here to Macau.

246
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,000
I understand.

247
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:47,480
Don't worry,

248
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:50,120
our colleagues at the Macau station

249
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:51,920
will investigate immediately.

250
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,250
If there's any news,

251
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,720
I'll get back to you as soon as possible.

252
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,520
I'll count on you then.

253
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,320
If this is true,

254
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:01,380
I need to start making preparations.

255
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:03,160
Then I'll take my leave.

256
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,240
Goodbye.

257
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:07,520
Thank you.

258
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:17,880
Lao Yi.

259
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,400
Sir.

260
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:27,840
This Director Shen from the government suspects

261
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,560
that our assassination attempt failed

262
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,760
because someone

263
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,330
inside our organization is a traitor.

264
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,720
A traitor?

265
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:38,160
That can't be.

266
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:41,080
When he said that,

267
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:43,320
my heart sank.

268
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,640
Logically speaking,

269
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,440
very few people knew about this.

270
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,160
How could the Japanese intelligence

271
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,820
have gotten the information?

272
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,200
In that case,

273
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:56,640
this matter

274
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:58,560
is indeed suspicious.

275
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:16,120
Do you think

276
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:19,720
among the people around us lately,

277
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:26,000
anyone seems off?

278
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,520
Is it him?

279
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:35,920
Don't say his name.

280
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:42,160
I know who you're talking about.

281
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,920
Keep this quiet.

282
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:49,840
Investigate secretly.

283
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:53,360
If you find anything suspicious,

284
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,640
find a way to test him.

285
00:19:58,480 --> 00:19:59,480
Understood.

286
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,920
Mr. Rong sent me to thank you.

287
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,400
Working for Mr. Rong

288
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,880
will be worth your while.

289
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:12,380
I don't want the money.

290
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,760
I'll pay whatever I owe you,

291
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,480
every damn cent.

292
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:20,520
Don't be so impulsive.

293
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:22,120
Cut the crap.

294
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:23,560
From now on,

295
